&lt;p&gt;The Delivery Manager / Senior Delivery Manager is responsible for driving complex healthcare technology implementations from early discovery through go-live and stabilization. This role sits at the center of client delivery and is expected to bring structure, urgency, and clarity to work that often starts out ambiguous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will serve as the operational owner across assigned accounts, partnering closely with clients, Product, Design, Engineering, Data, Clinical Solutions, and SLT. Your job is to turn scope, client priorities, discovery outputs, and technical inputs into a clear delivery path that teams can execute against. That means owning the plan, surfacing risks early, driving decisions, and making sure the right people are engaged at the right moments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a passive project tracking role. A successful Delivery Manager at Chorus actively leads delivery forward by shaping requirements, coordinating discovery and design, ensuring backlog readiness, managing governance, and preparing teams and clients for launch. You will be expected to create momentum, reduce churn, and ensure delivery stays aligned to scope, quality, timeline, and client outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client &amp;amp; Account Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the day-to-day delivery owner for assigned client accounts, ensuring clear visibility into priorities, status, risks, blockers, decisions, and next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operational rhythm of the account, including internal account team meetings, client delivery updates, RAID management, milestone tracking, and escalations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trust with client stakeholders through clear communication, follow-through, and thoughtful expectation management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure client commitments are tracked against scope, timeline, budget, and delivery capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery, Design &amp;amp; Requirements Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and coordinate discovery sessions with the appropriate Product, Design, Engineering, Data, Clinical, and client stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure discovery produces usable outputs, including workflow decisions, process flows, business rules, requirements, open questions, and follow-up actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product and Design to move from client input to validated requirements, concepts, designs, and implementation-ready artifacts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in workflows, requirements, edge cases, dependencies, data needs, and operational assumptions before work enters development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive documented alignment or written sign-off on key requirements and design decisions when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
