&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chorus Innovations is a fast-growing healthcare technology company with an adaptive platform as a service (PaaS) that enables the rapid development of mobile, desktop, text messaging and interactive voice applications. Chorus’ platform currently powers transformative healthcare, biomedical research and community health projects across institutions and public health agencies nationwide. We believe every community should have world-class health technology so they can thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is to improve the lives of people and communities by democratizing technology development in health and research.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Product Manager, you will own the vision, strategy, and evolution of key product lines within the Chorus platform. You will translate market needs, client patterns, and platform capabilities into clear product direction—balancing strategic foresight with the pragmatism needed to drive outcomes in a complex healthcare ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work at the intersection of R&amp;amp;D, Delivery, and Go-To-Market, ensuring each product area has well-defined goals, reusable templates, and a roadmap that reduces swirl, increases reuse, and unlocks scalable growth. You’ll define problems deeply, synthesize insights from users, clinical experts, research, and stakeholders, and convert them into product requirements, sequencing, and standards that elevate how solutions are built across Chorus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior leader on the Product team, you will champion clarity, prioritization, and measurable impact. You will shape product narratives, guide cross-functional alignment, and create the artifacts—requirements, stories, templates, and playbooks—that enable both Delivery teams and external partners to move faster with higher quality. Your work ensures that each product line evolves intentionally, customers experience consistent value, and the platform advances toward our long-term vision of intelligent, scalable healthcare infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the vision and roadmap for behavioral health workflows across intake, referrals, crisis response, care coordination, and ongoing case management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate real-world behavioral health practices, policy changes, and user insights into clear product requirements, workflow definitions, and reusable templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Clinical Solutions, Design, Engineering, and Delivery to ensure features are feasible, well-sequenced, and aligned to product standards and platform capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify cross-client patterns to create scalable, repeatable modules that reduce customization and accelerate delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve mobile-first behavioral health workflows optimized for frontline, in-field, and time-sensitive use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive FHIR-aligned workflow and data model design, ensuring behavioral health workflows integrate cleanly with EHRs, EDWs, crisis systems, and external partners through modern interoperability standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize roadmap decisions based on user value, strategic impact, regulatory alignment, and long-term scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure product performance and user outcomes to inform iteration and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support GTM, Partner Success, and Delivery teams with clear product artifacts that improve scoping, demos, and client alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
